SIMPLE: preclude
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preclude
<hw>Pre*clude"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Precluded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Precluding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>praecludere</ets>,
<ets>praeclusum</ets>; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>claudere</ets> to
shut. See <er>Close</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To put a
barrier before; hence, to shut out; to hinder; to stop; to
impede.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The valves <qex>preclude</qex> the blood from entering the
veins.</q> <rj><qau>E. Darwin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To shut out by anticipative action; to prevent or
hinder by necessary consequence or implication; to deter action of,
access to, employment of, etc.; to render ineffectual; to obviate by
anticipation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This much will obviate and <qex>preclude</qex> the objections.</q>
<rj><qau>Bentley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preclusion</ent>⟦br⟧
